SIMPLE: shameful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shameful
<hw>Shame"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Bringing
shame or disgrace; injurious to reputation; disgraceful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His naval preparations were not more surprising than his quick and
<qex>shameful</qex> retreat.</q> <rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exciting the feeling of shame in others; indecent;
<as>as, a <ex>shameful</ex> picture; a <ex>shameful</ex>
sight.</as></def> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Disgraceful; reproachful; indecent; unbecoming;
degrading; scandalous; ignominious; infamous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Shame"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Shame"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shameless</ent>⟦br⟧
